<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <title>Inflation API</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">
  <link href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:300' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>WELCOME TO JAMES'S INFLATION API</h1>
  <div class="wrapper">
    <h3>This API intended for developers to calculate inflation-adjusted values in current dollars. This API is RESTful and responses are in JSON format. Currently the API uses the Consumer Price Index, dating back to 1913. Future versions will allow developers to choose which ever economic index they prefer.
    <br/><br/>
    Consumer Price Index data is sourced from the <a href="https://www.minneapolisfed.org/community/teaching-aids/cpi-calculator-information/consumer-price-index-and-inflation-rates-1913">Federal Reserve Bank of Minneapolis</a>.
    </h3>
  </div>
  <h2>ENDPOINT</h2>
  <div class="wrapper">
  <h3>
      The endpoint for Consumer Price Index calculations is:
      <br><br>
      inflation-api.herokuapp.com/api/
  </h3>
  </div>
  <h2>PARAMETERS</h2>
  <div class="wrapper">
    <h3>
      <ul>
        <li>value</li>
        <li>year (1913-2021)</li>
      </ul>
      'Value' is the USD($) value to be adjusted for inflation.
      <br/><br/>
      'Year' is the desired year to adjust for inflation (ex: 1955).
      <br/><br/>
      To see the relative value of $100 in 1955, an example GET request would be:
      <br/><br/>
      inflation-api.herokuapp.com/api/?value=100&year=1955
    </h3>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
